Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAn apprentice, Emmanuel Boateng, has killed his friend, Nana Gyamfi, who is a 200 level student of the Kwame Nkrumah University of Technology.
According to GhanaWeb, the deceased had demanded the refund of a debt to enable him prepare for school.
Boateng told police that he decided to kill his friend because he couldnâ€™t raise the debt.
It was reported that Boateng lured the victim to his death under the guise of taking pictures of work on a plot of land he claimed his mother bought.
On the piece of land, he struck Gyamfi with a stick and fled.
Police in the Ashanti Region say neighbours who had seen them together earlier raised the alarm, after Gyamfi went missing.
